Protecting Consumers With Food-Safe Packaging

We have received an excellent audit rating by ASI Food Safety recognizing us as an SQF-Certified Company. The program follows the requirements outlined by Global Food Safety Initiative (GFSI).

This initiative aims to guarantee the safety of food products across the supply chain by setting standards to include flexible packaging for edibles like concentrate packaging, supplement packaging, snack packaging, and custom candy bags. GFSI ensures consistency and fosters continuous improvement in food safety practices including the manufacturing of custom pouch packaging such as custom cookie packaging and other custom-printed stand up pouches like those for cannabis edibles.

Learn more in our blog

Certified Child-Resistant Zipper

Choose our certified child-resistant zipper for flower and edibles to avoid having to repackage your goods when new laws hit the books. Our certified child-resistant zipper helps protect young children and keeps your goods fresh.

Ask about our Certified Child-Resistant packaging solutions.

*Our CR (Child Resistant) zipper has been evaluated and tested using the Consumer Product Safety Commission’s standards and certified by CR Testing Labs, LLC. Packaging was tested among participants ranging from 42 to 51 months of age. Senior adults also participated in the testing. The goal was to ensure children stay out, but seniors can get in.

At Sussex IM we offer our customers a wide range of services and molding applications that decrease costs and increase quality. Sussex IM runs over 65 injection molding machines – ranging from 25 to 725 tons and specializes in mid to high-volume production runs.

IML / IMD

In-molding labeling and In-mold decorating are an integrated part decorating technique wherein a decorative film, label or pre-form is placed into the mold prior to mold close and injection.

Decoration

Insert Molding

Over Molding

For over seventy years, the Tube Council of North America has been serving as supporting and advocating for the tube industry. Comprised of experts from within the industry, the Tube Council aims to serve as a resource for other tube professionals. By providing educational information, product and innovation updates, and other news, the Tube Council works to develop a strong network from every facet of the tube industry.

WHY JOIN THE TUBE COUNCIL?

The Tube Council of North America is dedicated to continuing a long tradition of leadership in the tube packaging industry and promoting the use of tubes with consumer goods product companies and consumers. The TCNA is also committed to providing members with the necessary tools to remain competitive in today’s challenging marketplace.

Membership in the TCNA is composed primarily of organizations engaged in producing products or services directly related to the North American collapsible squeeze tube industry.

Hayssen

For over 100 years, Hayssen has stood for reliable, innovative, and performant flexible packaging equipment and solutions. Headquartered in Duncan, South Carolina, and with facilities across the globe, Hayssen manufactures Vertical Form Fill Seal (VFFS) and Horizontal Flow Wrapping equipment used around the world.

Hayssen's packaging solutions have been deployed to wrap and bag products in food and food service, industrial and automotive, medical and pharmaceutical, and pet and animal food and care, and many other industries. Whether a single machine or an entire packaging line, Hayssen can deliver the flexible packaging solution to meet your needs and solve your challenges.

VIEW OUR CUSTOMER SUCCESS STORIES

History

The Hayssen brand began in 1910, when its founder, Herman Hayssen, invented and patented the first automatic bread wrapping machine in Sheboygan, Wisconsin. The first machines were manufactured in Mr. Hayssen's garage with the help of just one mechanic.

Hayssen was a privately-held and family-owned company from 1910 until 1966, when it became a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Bemis Company, a principal manufacturer of packaging materials and specialty coated and graphics products headquartered in Minneapolis, Minnesota. In May, 1997 Hayssen was acquired by Barry-Wehmiller and is now a BW Flexible Systems brand.

Bridge Analyzers, Inc. has exhaust gas analyzers, residual oxygen analyzers, MAP gas analyzers (modified atmosphere packaging), headspace gas analyzers and case ready meat gas analyzers. Applications include standard exhaust gas instruments used as diagnostic tools for mechanics to test tailpipe emissions. Specialized food packaging gas measurement in portable battery operated instruments provide food processors that are packaging using modified atmosphere packaging (MAP) processes a means to confirm that their packaging will deliver the extended shelf life which food manufacturers expect.

Modified Atmosphere Packaging (MAP) Gas Analyzers

MAP gas analyzers are used by food processors to confirm that their finished product package is fully sealed from air intrusion and incorporates the proper gas mixture to meet desired shelf life and product appearance standards. By reducing the oxygen levels in the final package the product shelf life can be extended. With the addition of CO2, anaerobic bacteria growth can be minimized. For case ready meat packing, the addition of very low levels of CO gas maintains the expected appearance of meat even in a low oxygen environment. Many fresh cut produce foods are packaged in modified atmosphere packaging including ready to eat salad bags, spinach, fresh cut apple slices, fresh snack packs and coffee.

Exhaust Gas Analyzers

EGA analyzers are used by fork lift service technicians, motorcycle enthusiasts, automotive repair facilities and indoor vehicle operators across North America to performance tune engines and/or diagnose and confirm proper exhaust emission levels. Our hand held units include a 2-gas, 4-gas and 5-gas analyzer. The 2-gas unit measures CO and HC. The 4-gas unit measures CO, CO2, O2 and HC. The 5-gas unit measures CO, CO2, O2, HC and NOx.

Packaging Machinery

Integrated End of Line Solutions to fit any industry’s packaging needs by providing state of the art automated robotic machinery.

Specialized Machinery

MWA prides itself on providing custom solutions for all of its clients; regardless of the industry or scope of the project, MWA is willing to find a solution tailored to fit all your industrial automation needs.

Standardized Machines

MWA offers a variety of industrial machinery designed with optimal efficiency in mind.  From secondary packaging to tertiary palletizers, MWA is able to find a simple resolution to any complicated obstacle.

Distribution Systems

MWA is experienced in various product orientation, disbursement, and transportation systems and will work to find the most effective method for distributing any product while always putting product integrity first.

Control System Retrofits

Recent control system advancements have made retrofitting a cost effective way of increasing a machine’s productivity and manageability.  MWA offers services for every level of retrofitting from developing a functional specification program to recommissioning machinery to fit today’s needs.

Systems Integration

MWA’s software engineers and programmers design and deliver complete systems integrating hardware with software to automate industrial machinery with process data.  MWA engineers are versed in every facet of automation software development from PLC and Motion Control/SCADA to HMI design.

Process Control

MWA improves processes and production efficiency by providing computer and control systems that collect and analyze data across control platforms all to a central location.

Industrial Services

MWA provides a wide array of design and support services including AutoCAD, project management, and remote data collection that will optimize production and increase overall efficiency.

 

Why choose MWA?
Versatility and Customization. Every MWA project is adapted for each customer utilizing a dynamic approach from design to implementation.
Experience. Over fifty years of combined experience developing complex packaging applications that utilize servo technology to not only enhance efficiency, but also minimize cost.
Complete Integration. MWA provides every customer a multifaceted approach to solve all their industrial automation needs, from packaging robotics to complete line and system integration with real time production data.

Leading Manufacturer of Quality Paper Products.

As a leading wholesale supplier of specialty paper products, Bocks Board Packaging is your go-to destination for high-quality packaging solutions. Our focus is on providing custom packaging options for businesses across various industries. With our expertise and commitment to excellence, we are dedicated to delivering top-notch products and exceptional customer service.

OUR PRODUCTS
Wholesale Specialty Paper Products

At Bocks Board Packaging, we take pride in offering a diverse selection of specialty paper products that elevate your packaging to the next level. Whether you require kraft paper for its natural and rustic appeal, corrugated cardboard for its strength and protection, or custom packaging solutions that showcase your brand’s uniqueness, we have you covered. Our range of specialty paper products is carefully curated to meet the demands of various industries, ensuring that you find the perfect packaging solution that aligns with your vision and requirements.

With our specialty paper products, you can enhance the presentation, durability, and sustainability of your packaging. We understand that each product deserves packaging that not only safeguards it but also enhances its appeal. That’s why we offer a diverse range of paper grades, finishes, and customization options to cater to your specific needs. Whether you’re looking for packaging that exudes elegance, durability, or eco-friendliness, our specialty paper products are designed to deliver exceptional results and create a lasting impression on your customers.

OUR PRODUCTS
Elevate Your Brand with Custom Packaging Solutions

Your packaging is an extension of your brand, and at Bocksboard Packaging, we understand the significance of making a memorable impression. Our custom packaging solutions are tailored to showcase your brand identity, values, and products. We believe that packaging should not only protect your items but also captivate your target audience and enhance their unboxing experience. Our dedicated team of experts will collaborate with you to understand your brand, design preferences, and packaging requirements. From concept to execution, we’ll guide you through the entire process to create custom packaging solutions that truly embody your brand’s essence.

With our custom packaging solutions, you have the freedom to choose from a wide range of materials, finishes, printing techniques, and embellishments to create packaging that stands out from the crowd. Whether you desire minimalist and sleek designs or vibrant and eye-catching artwork, we have the expertise to bring your vision to life. Our commitment to quality ensures that every detail of your custom packaging is meticulously executed, resulting in a finished product that aligns with your brand image and enhances the overall customer experience. Elevate your brand with packaging that speaks volumes about your commitment to quality, innovation, and attention to detail.

OUR PRODUCTS
Deliver Piping Hot Pizza with Our Premium Pizza Inserts

At Bocksboard Packaging, we understand that delivering a piping hot and delicious pizza is crucial for customer satisfaction. Our high-quality pizza inserts are designed to maintain the freshness, temperature, and integrity of your pizzas during transportation. Crafted from durable and heat-resistant materials, our pizza inserts provide excellent support and insulation to prevent any damage or sogginess. With our reliable pizza inserts, you can ensure that your customers receive their pizzas in perfect condition, ready to be enjoyed.

Our pizza inserts come in various sizes and configurations to accommodate different pizza box dimensions. Whether you specialize in thin crust, deep-dish, or stuffed crust pizzas, we have the right inserts to suit your specific needs. Our team can also assist you in customizing the inserts with your branding or promotional messages, helping you leave a lasting impression on your customers. Trust Bocksboard Packaging to enhance your pizza delivery experience and elevate your brand’s reputation for exceptional taste and quality.

ABOUT US
Embrace Sustainability with Our Eco-Friendly Packaging Solutions

We believe in the importance of sustainable packaging that minimizes environmental impact without compromising on functionality and appeal. Our sustainable packaging solutions are designed to help you align your brand with eco-conscious values while meeting your packaging needs. We offer a range of recyclable, compostable, and biodegradable materials that reduce waste and promote a circular economy. By choosing our eco-friendly packaging, you not only contribute to a greener future but also resonate with environmentally conscious consumers who appreciate sustainable practices.

Our sustainable packaging solutions go beyond materials. We also focus on optimizing packaging design to minimize excess material usage, maximize space efficiency, and reduce carbon footprint during transportation. Our team of packaging experts will collaborate with you to create innovative and planet-friendly packaging solutions that align with your sustainability goals. Together, let’s make a positive impact on the environment while delivering exceptional products to your customers.

OUR PRODUCTS
Maintain Freshness and Flavor with our Premium Butcher Paper

When it comes to packaging and storing meat products, maintaining freshness, flavor, and quality is of utmost importance. Bocksboard Packaging offers a range of premium meat paper products that are specially designed to preserve the integrity and extend the shelf life of your meat. Our high-grade meat paper provides excellent breathability, moisture control, and protection against external contaminants, ensuring that your meat products stay fresh and flavorful for longer periods.

Our meat paper is available in various sizes and formats to accommodate different cuts of meat, including steaks, poultry, sausages, and more. It is specifically engineered to enhance the natural maturation process while preventing excessive moisture loss or absorption. With our meat paper, you can confidently showcase your meat products while assuring customers of their quality and freshness. Trust Bocksboard Packaging to provide you with the ideal meat paper solutions that meet your specific requirements and maintain the excellence of your meat offerings.

CONTACT US
Elevate Your Brand with Customized Packaging Solutions

Your packaging plays a crucial role in conveying your brand story and capturing the attention of your customers. At Bocksboard Packaging, we understand the importance of customization and offer tailored packaging solutions that align with your brand identity. Our team of skilled designers and engineers collaborate closely with you to create packaging that not only protects your products but also showcases your brand’s personality, values, and uniqueness. With our customized packaging solutions, you can elevate your brand and leave a lasting impression on your customers.

Whether you need custom shapes, sizes, printing, or special finishes, we have the capabilities to bring your vision to life. Our state-of-the-art facilities and advanced printing technologies ensure the highest quality standards for your packaging. From concept to production, our team is dedicated to delivering exceptional results that exceed your expectations. Experience the power of customized packaging and let Bocksboard Packaging help you create packaging that resonates with your target audience and enhances your brand recognition.

OUR FRUIT

EXCEPTIONAL FRUIT, YEAR-ROUND, GLOBALLY

Growing fruit today is increasingly scientific, but it is also still an art and that is what sets RemBrandt® Fruit from E.W. Brandt & Sons apart.

We’ve embraced the latest advances in fruit production and packaging. In fact, we’ve innovated a few of them ourselves. Our quality assurance program is second to none.

But we’ve also held fast to the belief that there is no substitute for experience and judgment. We know the only way to assure consistently top-quality fruit is by hands-on attention to detail, day in and day out. From cultivation and harvest to packing, storage and shipping, the Brandt family intensively manages every aspect of production with one goal in mind: making sure our fruit arrives at your store fresh and flavorful – nature’s masterpiece at its best.

OUR STANDARDS

WE STRIVE FOR EXCELLENCE

E.W. Brandt & Son’s has long been at the forefront of quality standards and food safety. We were the first fruit company in the United States to be certified SQF 2000 Level 3 and we’ve built a global reputation for exceptional high-quality fruit from this rigorous international standard.

Our commitment to quality starts in the orchard. RemBrandt® Fruit comes from two sources: The orchards we own, also known as TLC Orchards and from a select group of growers who meet our quality/safety criteia. We stay consistent in managing the cultivation and harvesting process by sometimes picking from the same tree as many as 3 times to reach that optimum sweetness & color.

That same commitment overflows into our state of the art quality control system. With this system that is in place we can provide detailed data and control across every aspect of our operation. Also allowing us to meticulously manage and track every single box of fruit that we deliver because of it’s specific/unique design for the fruit industry. Behind these systems and processes, we at RemBrandt® Fruit foster a culture of excellence. From that culture we set ourselves apart by placing our people in the right areas and personally oversee ever detail.

ABOUT US

E.W. BRANDT & SONS, INC. HISTORY

Growing fruit is in the Brandt family blood. We’ve been farming in the Yakima Valley since 1947 when Everette and Ada Brandt purchased 16 acres of peaches and cherries.  Since then, we have grown the company exponentially and ship our fruit to all major domestic markets and international markets.  Currently, the company is owned and operated by brothers Allen and Dana Brandt.  Allen is the CEO and Dana is Vice President of Operations.

We are all aware of smaller size containers being produced. When that happens, there can be many implications throughout the production line. One such a case came to us from a major cereal producer who had downsized the fill but needed to keep the store facing space. Once the cases were filled with cartons, the footprint to height ratio made the case unstable on its own. With a long distance from the case packer to the palletizer, ups, downs and turns caused the cases to tip over and stop the line.

The solution in the customers mind was to combine multiple cases together creating a bundle that could travel in a stable condition. With pallet patterns being different for different SKU's, they asked about combining cases in groups of 2 or 3 and allow pass-through capability for more stable cases. In testing, they discovered they could glue cases together with an adhesive that would hold the cases through transport, be palletized and stretch wrapped. 24 hours later, the adhesive would dissolve, and all the cases would be singles again, ready for distribution.

The Emerald team brainstormed with the customer to develop a methodology that would outpace the capability of the case packer. Unlike typical adhesive that sets in less than a second, we needed about 2.5 seconds of compression for this formula.

The Combiner accepts up to 16 cases per minute, allowing the first case into the compression, moved out of the way to allow a second case to have adhesive applied and combined with the first with dual servo controlled overhead compression plates. A third case is released, glued and combined with the first two. The bundle is released to a rotator section where the bundle is turned 90° either clockwise or counterclockwise.

Read More







A fulfillment company came to Emerald Automation to find a machine that would load bags of various products into standard RSC cases. As a FANUC Authorized Integrator, we offered a solution to use a robot with a spatula as an end effector.

After accepting filled and sealed bags, we grabbed the completed bag and laid it down on a bag checkweigher infeed. The bag is then checked for proper weight and transferred onto an incline conveyor up to the robot tool. When the bag reaches the top of the conveyor, the bag is deposited onto the spatula tool. With the bag in place, the Robot moves, inserting the end arm and tool into the box, tilting the tool to leave the bag flat at one end of the case. On the next bag, the robot places the bag at the other end of the case, creating a 2 x 1 layer pattern. The process continues until the proper bag count is achieved. Depending on the order, they can load as little as 10 or up to 42 bags per case.

Read More







With more and more focus being put on Sanitary Designs for food production facilities, Emerald responded by changing our Dash-DP wash-down design to eliminate tubular frames and moved to an open design to eliminate the opportunity for bacteria to settle and collect in tight locations where chemicals and water can't get. The formed Stainless Plates and standoffs leave plenty of room to apply cleaning chemicals and water to rinse the machines. We even upgraded the electrical components to stainless construction, eliminating the need to bag parts of the packer or the whole packer during clean-up. This saves time for the operators to get the job done.




Here at Emerald Automation, we listen to the needs of our customer to build machinery to live in their "real world" environment. We didn't just take the existing design and make it somewhat wash-down, we started with a clean sheet. If you have a need for a sanitary design casepacker, give us a call or email us at sales@emeraldautomation.com.

Read More








A customer came to Emerald needing a Bulk Product Case Packer (Dash-BP). They also required Lane Product Infeed Guides for existing Product Conveyor with transition to Loader Infeed. Other requirements included: A hinged Pass Through Conveyor (for access). The ability to merge onto Loader Laned Variable Speed Infeed Conveyors. An Acceleration Belt for product separation. Product counting by lane. Polycarbonate Guard Packaging with Safety Interlock.

Emerald was able to fulfill all the customers requirements for packing the product and integrating multiple conveyors and existing equipment into a seamless operation. Our Design Engineers are able to custom build every machine to the specific requirements of every customer. Our System Integrators are able to integrate our products into any existing system.

Buy Equipment

We Know Equipment

SIGMA Group stands as a global leader in the processing and packaging industry, driving the circular economy through our innovative marketplace platforms. Our mission is to activate a self-sustaining cycle of value creation through the reuse of surplus equipment.

Within our platforms, an ecosystem thrives where sellers and buyers converge, fostering a continuous flow of assets from one user to the next. This promotes sustainable reuse and allows equipment to be repurposed in a new capacity.

When surplus assets are reused, their lifespan extends, creating maximum value while minimizing waste. This approach not only benefits sellers and buyers but also resonates with stakeholders invested in sustainable progress.

SIGMA Group’s commitment to igniting a positive network sets the stage for a future where circular principles drive commerce, paving the way for enhanced value and a greener tomorrow.
